---
import type { CollectionEntry } from 'astro:content';
export interface Props { font: CollectionEntry<'fonts'>['data']; }
const { font } = Astro.props;
const fam = font.fontFamily;
---
<div class="iu" style={`--fam:${fam}`}>

  <!-- 01 — INTERACTIVE READER UI: real-scale long-form editorial with weight slider + feature toggles -->
  <figure class="iu__item">
    <figcaption class="iu__cap"><span class="index-num">01</span><span class="label">Reader UI — long-form editorial at real scale (interactive)</span></figcaption>
    <div class="iu__scene">
      <div class="iu__device lrdr" data-lrdr>
        <div class="iu__chrome">
          <div class="iu__dots"><i></i><i></i><i></i></div>
          <span class="iu__addr">meridian.press/essays/the-warmth-of-a-brushed-letter</span>
        </div>

        <div class="lrdr__bar">
          <span class="lrdr__logo">Meridian</span>
          <nav class="lrdr__feats" aria-label="Reading controls">
            <label class="lrdr__wlabel">
              <span>Weight <i data-wout>400</i></span>
              <input type="range" data-waxis min="400" max="700" step="1" value="400" aria-label="Font weight" />
            </label>
            <button class="is-on" data-feat="liga" aria-pressed="true">Ligatures</button>
            <button data-feat="tnum" aria-pressed="false">Tabular</button>
            <button data-feat="frac" aria-pressed="false">Fractions</button>
          </nav>
          <span class="lrdr__time">7 min</span>
        </div>

        <div class="lrdr__chip" aria-hidden="true">
          <span class="lrdr__chiplabel">Live</span>
          <span class="lrdr__chipspec" data-chip>fi fl office — ¾</span>
        </div>

        <article class="lrdr__body" data-text>
          <span class="lrdr__kicker">Essay · On Type</span>
          <h4 class="lrdr__head">The warmth of a brushed letter</h4>
          <p class="lrdr__byline">Oluwaseun Adeyemi · <span class="lrdr__fig">14 June 2026</span> · <span class="lrdr__fig">7</span> min</p>
          <p class="lrdr__lede"><span class="lrdr__drop">T</span>here is a quality in certain typefaces — the ones that were drawn with a brush rather than ruled with a pen — that you feel before you can name it. The fi and fl ligatures close; the office of letters settles into a harmony; and the column acquires the warmth of something written, not composed.</p>
          <p>Lora carries that quality into every screen it inhabits. Set in a <span class="lrdr__fig">1/2</span>-column measure on a device running at <span class="lrdr__fig">326</span> ppi, it holds an even, inviting colour. The serifs bracket firmly; the stress angles slightly back toward the pen. Drag the weight up and the texture deepens without ever going harsh — the brushed origins keep it supple.</p>
          <blockquote class="lrdr__quote">A typeface that was drawn for the screen does not merely survive it; it belongs there.</blockquote>
          <p>The calligraphic root is never decorative. It is structural: those softened terminals are precisely the reason a column of Lora at <span class="lrdr__fig">16</span>px feels like the work of a careful hand, not a typesetting engine.</p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
    <p class="iu__hint label">Drag the weight slider (400–700), toggle ligatures, tabular figures, and fractions — the Live chip and the column change instantly.</p>
  </figure>

  <!-- 02 — LITERARY MAGAZINE SPREAD: drop cap, italic pull quote, driving serifs at display scale -->
  <figure class="iu__item">
    <figcaption class="iu__cap"><span class="index-num">02</span><span class="label">Literary spread — drop cap, italic pull quote, brushed display</span></figcaption>
    <div class="iu__scene scene-lit">
      <div class="iu__poster lit" data-lit>
        <!-- verso: full-bleed headline + kicker -->
        <section class="lit__verso">
          <span class="lit__kicker">Fiction · Issue <span class="lit__num">23</span></span>
          <h3 class="lit__title">Every Letter<br/><em class="lit__ital">Written Twice</em></h3>
          <p class="lit__sub">A story about a correspondence that outlasted the correspondents, and the typeface that held it together.</p>
        </section>
        <!-- recto: body text with drop cap + pull quote -->
        <section class="lit__recto">
          <p class="lit__body"><span class="lit__drop">T</span>he letters arrived every Tuesday without fail, in envelopes the colour of old cream, the address written in a hand that had never entirely left school. Inside, the sentences were long and considered, full of parenthetical qualifications, the way a person writes when they have all afternoon and nobody to interrupt them.</p>
          <p class="lit__body">She kept them in a box under her writing desk, tied with a length of green ribbon she had cut from a hat she no longer wore. Each one dated, each one smelling faintly of the cedar drawer where the box had spent its winters.</p>
          <blockquote class="lit__pull"><em>The letter is the one form that waits for you. It does not refresh itself; it simply sits there, patient, until you are ready to read it again.</em></blockquote>
          <p class="lit__body">What surprised her, rereading them after he was gone, was how many of them were really about the act of writing itself — the pleasure of choosing a word, the small decisions of spacing and margin that constituted a kind of care.</p>
          <footer class="lit__foot">
            <span class="lit__folio">24</span>
            <span class="lit__mag">Meridian Review</span>
            <span class="lit__folio">25</span>
          </footer>
        </section>
      </div>
    </div>
    <p class="iu__hint label">A two-page literary spread — brushed drop cap, italic pull quote, even body colour at paragraph scale. Hover to reveal the accent rule.</p>
  </figure>

  <!-- 03 — PUBLISHER BRAND / WORDMARK: italic + weight interplay, tnum in colophon, SVG rule -->
  <figure class="iu__item">
    <figcaption class="iu__cap"><span class="index-num">03</span><span class="label">Brand — a literary publisher identity &amp; catalogue page</span></figcaption>
    <div class="iu__scene scene-brand">
      <div class="iu__poster brand" data-brand>
        <!-- left: editorial identity card -->
        <div class="brand__side brand__side--ident">
          <div class="brand__ident">
            <span class="brand__press">Meridian Press</span>
            <h3 class="brand__name">Meridian</h3>
            <span class="brand__tag"><em>Independent Publishers Since <span class="brand__fig">1987</span></em></span>
            <svg class="brand__rule" viewBox="0 0 280 8" fill="none" aria-hidden="true" preserveAspectRatio="xMidYMid meet">
              <line class="brand__line" x1="0" y1="4" x2="280" y2="4" stroke="var(--accent)" stroke-width="1.5"/>
              <circle cx="140" cy="4" r="3" fill="var(--accent)"/>
            </svg>
            <p class="brand__genres">Fiction · Poetry · Essays · Translation</p>
          </div>
          <dl class="brand__stats">
            <div>
              <dd><span class="brand__fig">38</span></dd>
              <dt>Years</dt>
            </div>
            <div>
              <dd><span class="brand__fig">1,248</span></dd>
              <dt>Titles</dt>
            </div>
            <div>
              <dd><span class="brand__fig">34</span></dd>
              <dt>Languages</dt>
            </div>
          </dl>
          <span class="brand__foot">meridian.press</span>
        </div>
        <!-- right: current season catalogue -->
        <div class="brand__side brand__side--cat">
          <span class="brand__season">Spring <span class="brand__fig">2026</span> Catalogue</span>
          <ul class="brand__list">
            <li class="brand__entry" data-hover>
              <span class="brand__num brand__fig">01</span>
              <div class="brand__info">
                <span class="brand__etitle"><em>The Cartographer's Widow</em></span>
                <span class="brand__eaut">Priya Nair</span>
              </div>
              <span class="brand__eprice brand__fig">£14.99</span>
            </li>
            <li class="brand__entry" data-hover>
              <span class="brand__num brand__fig">02</span>
              <div class="brand__info">
                <span class="brand__etitle"><em>Seventeen Letters</em></span>
                <span class="brand__eaut">Marco Calderón</span>
              </div>
              <span class="brand__eprice brand__fig">£12.99</span>
            </li>
            <li class="brand__entry" data-hover>
              <span class="brand__num brand__fig">03</span>
              <div class="brand__info">
                <span class="brand__etitle"><em>The Weight of Silence</em></span>
                <span class="brand__eaut">Yuki Tanaka</span>
              </div>
              <span class="brand__eprice brand__fig">£16.50</span>
            </li>
            <li class="brand__entry" data-hover>
              <span class="brand__num brand__fig">04</span>
              <div class="brand__info">
                <span class="brand__etitle"><em>Archipelago</em></span>
                <span class="brand__eaut">Fatima Al-Rashid</span>
              </div>
              <span class="brand__eprice brand__fig">£13.99</span>
            </li>
            <li class="brand__entry" data-hover>
              <span class="brand__num brand__fig">05</span>
              <div class="brand__info">
                <span class="brand__etitle"><em>All That Remains</em></span>
                <span class="brand__eaut">David Osei-Bonsu</span>
              </div>
              <span class="brand__eprice brand__fig">£11.99</span>
            </li>
          </ul>
          <p class="brand__note">Prices in tabular figures — columns align regardless of digit width.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <p class="iu__hint label">A publisher identity split across a wordmark panel and a spring catalogue — italic titles, tabular price figures that align in columns, and an SVG rule that draws on hover.</p>
  </figure>

  <!-- 04 — FEATURE OPENER: weight-axis headline that breathes on scroll, italic/roman interplay -->
  <figure class="iu__item">
    <figcaption class="iu__cap"><span class="index-num">04</span><span class="label">Feature opener — weight-breathing headline, italic/roman interplay</span></figcaption>
    <div class="iu__scene scene-open">
      <div class="iu__poster opener" data-opener>
        <span class="op__issue">Meridian Review · No. <span class="op__num">23</span> · Summer <span class="op__num">2026</span></span>
        <div class="op__center">
          <span class="op__over">A special feature on</span>
          <h3 class="op__title" data-breather>The Calligraphic<br/><em class="op__em">Imagination</em></h3>
          <span class="op__rule" aria-hidden="true" data-rule></span>
          <p class="op__stand">How a generation of type designers learned to give the screen a letter shaped not by a ruler, but by a brush held at an angle — and what that warmth does to the act of reading.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="op__foot">
          <span class="op__by">Essay by <em>Isabela Ferreira</em></span>
          <span class="op__pp">pp. <span class="op__num">12–21</span></span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <p class="iu__hint label">Hover the opener — the headline breathes to bold (700) as the rule draws across, dramatising Lora's full weight range.</p>
  </figure>

</div>

<script>
  // ---- 01 READER UI: weight slider + feature toggles ----
  document.querySelectorAll<HTMLElement>('[data-lrdr]').forEach((rdr) => {
    const text = rdr.querySelector<HTMLElement>('[data-text]')!;
    const chip = rdr.querySelector<HTMLElement>('[data-chip]')!;
    const wout = rdr.querySelector<HTMLElement>('[data-wout]')!;
    const waxis = rdr.querySelector<HTMLInputElement>('[data-waxis]')!;
    const state: Record<string, boolean> = { liga: true, tnum: false, frac: false };
    let wght = 400;

    const chipTexts: Record<string, string> = {
      default: 'fi fl office — ¾',
      tnum:    '1 234 — 567 890',
      frac:    '1/2 and 3/4 done',
    };

    const apply = () => {
      const feats = `'liga' ${state.liga ? 1 : 0}, 'tnum' ${state.tnum ? 1 : 0}, 'frac' ${state.frac ? 1 : 0}`;
      text.style.fontFeatureSettings = feats;
      text.style.fontVariationSettings = `'wght' ${wght}`;
      chip.style.fontFeatureSettings = feats;
      chip.style.fontVariationSettings = `'wght' ${wght}`;
      chip.textContent = state.frac ? chipTexts.frac : state.tnum ? chipTexts.tnum : chipTexts.default;
    };

    waxis.addEventListener('input', () => {
      wght = +waxis.value;
      wout.textContent = String(wght);
      apply();
    });

    rdr.querySelectorAll<HTMLButtonElement>('[data-feat]').forEach((btn) => {
      const feat = btn.dataset.feat!;
      btn.addEventListener('click', () => {
        state[feat] = !state[feat];
        btn.classList.toggle('is-on', state[feat]);
        btn.setAttribute('aria-pressed', String(state[feat]));
        apply();
      });
    });

    apply();
  });

  // ---- 03 BRAND: SVG rule length + catalogue row selection ----
  document.querySelectorAll<HTMLElement>('[data-brand]').forEach((card) => {
    const line = card.querySelector<SVGLineElement>('.brand__line');
    if (line) {
      const len = Math.ceil((line as any).getTotalLength?.() ?? 280);
      line.style.setProperty('--rule-len', String(len));
    }
    // clicking a catalogue row marks it as "selected"
    card.querySelectorAll<HTMLElement>('[data-hover]').forEach((row) => {
      row.addEventListener('click', () => {
        card.querySelectorAll('[data-hover]').forEach(r => r.classList.remove('is-selected'));
        row.classList.add('is-selected');
      });
    });
  });

  // ---- 04 OPENER: headline breathes on hover + rule draws on scroll-into-view ----
  document.querySelectorAll<HTMLElement>('[data-opener]').forEach((op) => {
    const rule = op.querySelector<HTMLElement>('[data-rule]')!;
    if (!rule) return;

    const reduce = window.matchMedia('(prefers-reduced-motion: reduce)').matches;
    if (reduce) {
      rule.classList.add('is-drawn');
      return;
    }

    // Ensure rule starts hidden, then animate when scene is substantially in view
    rule.classList.remove('is-drawn');
    const io = new IntersectionObserver((entries, obs) => {
      entries.forEach((e) => {
        if (!e.isIntersecting) return;
        // Small rAF delay ensures browser has had a chance to paint the hidden state
        requestAnimationFrame(() => {
          requestAnimationFrame(() => {
            rule.classList.add('is-drawn');
            obs.disconnect();
          });
        });
      });
    }, { threshold: 0.85 });
    io.observe(op);
  });
</script>

<style>
  .iu__item { margin: 0; }
  .iu__hint { margin-top: var(--sp-2); color: var(--fg-3); }
  .iu__scene * { font-family: var(--fam); }

  /* ============================================================
     01 — READER UI (real px, interactive)
     ============================================================ */
  .lrdr {
    font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.5;
    display: flex; flex-direction: column;
    min-height: 640px;
  }

  .lrdr__bar {
    display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 0.9rem;
    padding: 0.55rem 1rem; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line);
    flex-wrap: wrap; row-gap: 0.4rem;
  }
  .lrdr__logo {
    font-size: 20px; font-weight: 600; color: var(--fg);
    letter-spacing: 0.01em; font-style: italic;
    font-variation-settings: 'wght' 600;
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }
  .lrdr__feats {
    display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 0.5rem;
    margin-left: auto; flex-wrap: wrap;
  }
  .lrdr__wlabel {
    display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 0.4rem;
    font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 10.5px; letter-spacing: 0.04em;
    color: var(--fg-3); white-space: nowrap;
  }
  .lrdr__wlabel i { font-style: normal; color: var(--accent); min-width: 2.4ch; }
  .lrdr__wlabel input[type='range'] {
    -webkit-appearance: none; appearance: none;
    width: 68px; height: 2px; background: var(--line); border-radius: 2px; cursor: pointer;
  }
  .lrdr__wlabel input[type='range']::-webkit-slider-thumb {
    -webkit-appearance: none; appearance: none;
    width: 12px; height: 12px; border-radius: 50%;
    background: var(--accent); border: 2px solid var(--bg);
    box-shadow: 0 0 0 1px var(--accent);
  }
  .lrdr__wlabel input[type='range']::-moz-range-thumb {
    width: 12px; height: 12px; border-radius: 50%;
    background: var(--accent); border: 2px solid var(--bg);
  }
  .lrdr__feats button {
    font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 10.5px; letter-spacing: 0.04em;
    color: var(--fg-3); padding: 0.3rem 0.55rem; border-radius: 100px;
    border: 1px solid var(--line); cursor: pointer; transition: all 0.18s var(--ease);
    white-space: nowrap;
  }
  .lrdr__feats button:hover { color: var(--fg); border-color: var(--fg-3); }
  .lrdr__feats button.is-on {
    color: var(--accent-contrast); background: var(--accent); border-color: var(--accent);
  }
  .lrdr__time {
    font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 11px; color: var(--fg-3);
    letter-spacing: 0.06em; padding-left: 0.5rem; border-left: 1px solid var(--line);
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }

  /* magnified specimen chip */
  .lrdr__chip {
    display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 0.65rem;
    padding: 0.5rem 1rem; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line);
    background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--accent) 6%, var(--bg));
  }
  .lrdr__chiplabel {
    font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 10px; letter-spacing: 0.14em;
    text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--accent-contrast);
    background: var(--accent); border-radius: 100px; padding: 0.12rem 0.5rem;
    white-space: nowrap; flex-shrink: 0;
  }
  .lrdr__chipspec {
    font-size: clamp(17px, 3.5cqi, 22px); line-height: 1; color: var(--fg); letter-spacing: -0.01em;
  }

  /* article body */
  .lrdr__body {
    padding: clamp(1.2rem, 3cqi, 2.4rem) clamp(1.2rem, 4.5cqi, 3.5rem);
    max-width: 68ch; margin: 0 auto;
    overflow-y: auto;
    flex: 1 1 0;
    min-height: 0;
  }
  .lrdr__kicker {
    font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 11px; letter-spacing: 0.14em;
    text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--accent);
  }
  .lrdr__head {
    font-size: clamp(24px, 4cqi, 34px); line-height: 1.1; margin: 0.5rem 0 0.55rem;
    font-weight: 600; letter-spacing: -0.01em; color: var(--fg);
    font-variation-settings: 'wght' 600;
  }
  .lrdr__byline {
    font-size: 13px; color: var(--fg-3); font-style: italic; margin: 0 0 1.3rem;
  }
  .lrdr__fig { font-feature-settings: inherit; }
  .lrdr__lede, .lrdr__body p {
    font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.68; color: var(--fg); margin: 0 0 1em;
  }
  .lrdr__lede { font-size: 17px; }
  .lrdr__drop {
    float: left; font-size: 3.15em; line-height: 0.72; padding: 0.04em 0.13em 0 0;
    color: var(--accent); font-weight: 700;
    font-variation-settings: 'wght' 700;
  }
  .lrdr__quote {
    font-size: 19px; line-height: 1.4; font-style: italic; color: var(--fg);
    border-left: 2.5px solid var(--accent); padding-left: 1.1rem; margin: 1.4rem 0;
  }

  @media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
    .lrdr__feats button { transition: none; }
  }

  /* ============================================================
     02 — LITERARY SPREAD (container-query print sizing)
     ============================================================ */
  .scene-lit > .iu__poster { position: relative; inset: auto; }
  .lit {
    background: var(--bg); color: var(--fg);
    display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    font-feature-settings: 'liga' 1, 'kern' 1;
    container-type: inline-size;
  }
  .lit__verso, .lit__recto {
    padding: 6cqi 5.5cqi 5.5cqi;
  }
  .lit__verso {
    display: flex; flex-direction: column; justify-content: center; gap: 3.5cqi;
    background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--accent) 5%, var(--bg));
    border-right: 1px solid var(--line-soft);
  }
  .lit__kicker {
    font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 2.1cqi; letter-spacing: 0.18em;
    text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--accent);
  }
  .lit__num { font-feature-settings: 'tnum' 1; }
  .lit__title {
    font-size: 9.5cqi; line-height: 0.96; font-weight: 600; margin: 0;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em; color: var(--fg);
    font-variation-settings: 'wght' 600;
  }
  .lit__ital { font-style: italic; display: block; color: var(--accent); }
  .lit__sub {
    font-size: 2.7cqi; line-height: 1.5; color: var(--fg-2); font-style: italic;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--line-soft); padding-top: 3cqi; max-width: 36ch;
  }

  /* recto body */
  .lit__recto { display: flex; flex-direction: column; }
  .lit__body {
    font-size: 2.5cqi; line-height: 1.65; color: var(--fg);
    margin: 0 0 0.9em; text-indent: 1.6em; text-align: justify; hyphens: auto;
  }
  .lit__body:first-of-type { text-indent: 0; }
  .lit__drop {
    float: left; font-size: 10.5cqi; line-height: 0.74; padding: 0.45cqi 1.2cqi 0 0;
    color: var(--accent); font-weight: 700; font-variation-settings: 'wght' 700;
  }
  .lit__pull {
    border-left: 0; border-top: 1px solid var(--line-soft);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line-soft);
    margin: 3cqi 0; padding: 2.5cqi 0;
    font-size: 3.1cqi; line-height: 1.45; color: var(--fg-2); font-style: normal;
    text-align: center; text-indent: 0;
  }
  .lit__pull em { font-style: italic; color: var(--fg); }
  .lit__foot {
    display: flex; justify-content: space-between; align-items: center;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--line-soft); padding-top: 2.5cqi; margin-top: auto;
  }
  .lit__folio {
    font-size: 2.1cqi; color: var(--fg-3); letter-spacing: 0.04em;
    font-feature-settings: 'tnum' 1;
  }
  .lit__mag {
    font-size: 1.9cqi; letter-spacing: 0.14em; color: var(--fg-3);
    text-transform: uppercase; font-feature-settings: 'liga' 0;
  }

  /* settle animation on drop cap */
  @media (prefers-reduced-motion: no-preference) {
    .lit__drop { animation: lit-settle 1s var(--ease, ease-out) both; }
    @keyframes lit-settle {
      from { opacity: 0; transform: translateY(-0.05em); }
      to   { opacity: 1; transform: none; }
    }
  }

  /* ============================================================
     03 — PUBLISHER BRAND (two-column identity + catalogue)
     ============================================================ */
  .scene-brand > .iu__poster { position: relative; inset: auto; }
  .brand {
    background: var(--bg); color: var(--fg);
    display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1.9fr;
    container-type: inline-size;
    font-feature-settings: 'liga' 1;
    min-height: 60cqi;
  }
  .brand__side { padding: 4cqi; }
  .brand__side--cat { padding-right: 3cqi; }
  .brand__side--ident {
    background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--accent) 5%, var(--bg));
    border-right: 1px solid var(--line-soft);
    display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 0; justify-content: space-between;
  }
  .brand__ident {
    display: flex; flex-direction: column; align-items: flex-start; gap: 2cqi;
  }
  .brand__press {
    font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 2.1cqi; letter-spacing: 0.2em;
    text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--fg-3);
  }
  .brand__name {
    font-size: 11cqi; line-height: 0.9; font-weight: 600; margin: 0;
    letter-spacing: -0.025em; color: var(--fg); font-style: italic;
    font-variation-settings: 'wght' 600;
  }
  .brand__tag {
